  "texts": [
    "We designated LLMs as \"bystanders\" and posed questions focusing on moral judgment and moral behavior.",
    "For each question, we also sought the reason behind the judgment.",
    "The Q1 group evaluates LLMs' moral value judgments (moral cognition), while the Q2 group assesses their moral behavior judgments (moral character).",
    "Starting from the baseline scenario of beating, we identified 12 factors across the three dimensions of \"individual attributes,\" \"complex scenarios,\" and \"religion and culture,\" which are highly related to morality (see Table 1).",
    "These factors yielded a total of 26 distinct scenarios."
  ],
